ADDITIONAL TERM: MANDATORY ATTRIBUTION

In addition to the conditions of the MIT License above, any distribution,
derivative work, or product that uses this Software, in whole or in part, MUST
provide clear and visible attribution to the original project "GrowBox" and a
link to its original source repository. The attribution MUST appear in at
least one user-facing location, such as:

  - the product's documentation or README;
  - an "About", "Credits", or "Acknowledgements" screen or section; or
  - the notices that accompany a source or binary distribution.

The attribution must, at minimum, state "Based on GrowBox (<ORIGINAL_REPO_URL>)"
and retain the copyright notice above. Removing, hiding, or obscuring this
attribution is not permitted.

